Respected Sir / Madam,
Please note the following analysis on soft drinks in consumer goods sector.
1. Regular consumption of soft drinks is harmful for liver, kidney and pancreas; specifically it is not good for kids, children and diabetic people. Though, soft drinks is tasty and a good option for quenching thirst during hot summer, it is still not clear whether occasional consumption of cold soft drinks is good for health.
2. I have seen wastage of fruits on daily basis in various markets and retail outlets of Chennai, Kolkata and Howrah. Let us consider various perishable fruits. The most critical fruit is Banana; it is easily rotten and wasted in a large quantity within 2-3 days. The next critical fruits are mangoes, papaya, water melons, sapota (chiku), black berry, litchi, grapes and oranges. On the other hand, the poor people and cattle fast without getting food at low price due to lack of proper sales and distribution.
3. So what should be the ideal substitutes of soft drinks? it can be fresh fruit and fruit juices such as green coconut, coconut, banana, mango, water melon, grapes and papaya. The soft drinks companies are expected to explore product innovation, product life-cycle management and technology life cycle analysis to introduce health drinks based on fruit juice and milk globally in place of existing soft drinks. Caution: Preservatives, color, sweetener and other harmful ingredients such as alcohol
4. Is it possible to produce healthy alcoholic energy drinks as substitute of country liquor or booz at reasonable fair price for alcohol addicted folks by reducing the percentage of alcohol (e.g. Cognac)? As-is booz business needs purification – isn’t it?
5. It is possible to do various types of intelligent analysis such as SWOT, TLC and ‘7-S’ analysis (Scope- System-Structur
e-Staff / Resources – Skill Style Support – Security and Strategy) with the support of consumer goods specialists, chemical, food processing and biotechnology and of course business analysts. In fact, it is a question of product innovation of Pepsi, Coke, Thumps up, Limca, Miranda, Sprite and other colored health drinks and energy drinks......
Request for your thought and necessary initiatives on the above.
Regards.
Sumit Chakraborty

I immediately spilled the drink out and told my family to do the same.

Is your delivery and market team so incapable of doing minor checks to see if updated sticks are in stores or not?

If something is past expiration.. Can't you people just exchange that bottle and keep updated stock?
